<h2>
   Types of Salmon Found Near Medford
</h2>
<h3>
   Chinook (King) Salmon
</h3>
<p>
    The Rogue River is world-renowned for its Chinook runs. Both spring and fall Chinook can be found in these waters, with fall runs often being the most productive for sport fishing.
</p>
<h3>
    Coho (Silver) Salmon
</h3>
<p>
    Though less abundant than Chinook, Coho salmon are still available in select tributaries and estuary areas. They're known for their acrobatics and willingness to hit flashy lures.
</p>
<h3>
    Occasional Sockeye and Steelhead Mixes
</h3>
<p>
    While Sockeye are rare this far south, the Rogue often sees a healthy influx of steelhead, which provide bonus action and are often mistaken for smaller salmon when hooked.
</p>
